  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to examine the effect of Saxagliptin in the newly diagnosed
      people with pre-diabetes and obesity besides lifestyle intervention ,there to evaluate DPP 4
      inhibitors of reversing pre-diabetes curative effect to normal blood sugar, and observe its
      influences on the targets of obesity related metabolic abnormalities, to explore new ways for
      intervention on populations with pre-diabetes and obesity .
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Materials and Methods: This is a perspectiveness ,randomized, opening study, patients will be
      randomly assigned to the standarddose Saxagliptin group ,the lifestyle intervention group,the
      Metformin group and the low dose Saxagliptin group with a 6-month treatment period.

      Oral glucose tolerance test will examined before and 6 months post-treatment during the
      trial.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
